üèÅ FINAL ARC ‚Äî The Wrap-Up (Episodes 16‚Äì19)
üé• Episode 16 ‚Äî Spring Cloud Gateway Filters (Authentication, Rate Limiting, and Tracing at the Edge)
üéôÔ∏è Narration (spoken style)
Welcome back!
Now that our microservices are reliable, let‚Äôs make our API Gateway more powerful.
The gateway is the entry point to our system ‚Äî it‚Äôs the perfect place for cross-cutting concerns like:

Authentication & Authorization

Rate Limiting

Logging & Tracing

Today, we‚Äôll implement these using Spring Cloud Gateway filters.

üíª Demo
pom.xml:

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.cloud</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-cloud-starter-gateway</artifactId>
</dependency>
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-security</artifactId>
</dependency>
Custom Gateway Filter Example:

@Component
public class AuthFilter implements GlobalFilter, Ordered {
    @Override
    public Mono<Void> filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, GatewayFilterChain chain) {
        String token = exchange.getRequest().getHeaders().getFirst("Authorization");
        if (token == null || !token.startsWith("Bearer ")) {
            exchange.getResponse().setStatusCode(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED);
            return exchange.getResponse().setComplete();
        }
        return chain.filter(exchange);
    }

    @Override
    public int getOrder() {
        return -1;
    }
}
application.yml (routes + rate limiter):

spring:
  cloud:
    gateway:
      routes:
        - id: booking
          uri: lb://BOOKING-SERVICE
          predicates:
            - Path=/booking/**
          filters:
            - name: RequestRateLimiter
              args:
                redis-rate-limiter.replenishRate: 5
                redis-rate-limiter.burstCapacity: 10
üéØ Result: Unauthorized requests are blocked; users can only make a few requests per second.

üß† Recap
Our API Gateway is now smarter ‚Äî it handles authentication, throttling, and tracing ‚Äî keeping downstream services focused on business logic.

