üéôÔ∏è Narration
Logs are gold when something breaks.
Instead of checking 5 different services, let‚Äôs collect all logs into one place ‚Äî using ELK Stack.

üíª Demo
Run ELK with Docker:

docker-compose up -d
Configure each service:

logging:
  appender:
    console:
      enabled: true
    file:
      enabled: true
  file:
    name: LOGSTASH
    appender: logstash
    destination: localhost:5000
Send logs ‚Üí Logstash ‚Üí Elasticsearch ‚Üí visualize in Kibana.

üß† Recap
With centralized logging, we can search all microservices logs by traceId ‚Äî perfect for debugging production issues.

